          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Targets of nominally 1.0 g in weight with an area",
                " thickness of 2.36 g/cm2 were prepared by compacting",
                " anhydrous CsF powder (99.99%, Sigma-Aldrich, USA) in a",
                " punch-and-die set using a hydraulic press."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "3HUNDEB"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 20 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EDEG",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC",
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The target discs were thick enough to completely stop",
                " the beam at the primary proton energy 17.5 MeV.",
                "During bombardment, each target had a Cu monitor foil",
                " in front with a nominal thickness of 0.025 mm.",
                "The incident energy on target was adjusted by means of",
                " Al degrader foils of various thicknesses located",
                " upstream from the monitor foils and targets.",
                "Each bombardment lasted about 85 min at a beam current",
                " of nominally 50 nA.",
                "The targets were bombarded in a small target holder",
                " mounted on the end of an external beamline,",
                " electrically insulated.",
                "As CsF is very hygroscopic, the targets were kept in a",
                " vacuum oven at a temperature of 150 C until shortly",
                " before irradiation.",
                "The targets were in a vacuum environment during",
                " bombardment.",
                "Following irradiation, each activated CsF disc was",
                " dissolved in 3 mL of water in a standard glass serum",
                " vial, that constituted the counting sources.",
                "Two identical fractions of the 133Ba solution were",
                " prepared into sources, a source having a point",
                " geometry and the other made up into a 3 mL solution.",
                "The two specially prepared 133Ba sources were identical",
                " in strength.",
                "The ratio of their respective detector responses",
                " provided a correction factor for the different",
                " counting geometry and the self-absorption in the",
                " liquid volume and glass walls.",
                "Decay data were taken from Firestone and Eckstrom,",
                " Table of radioactive isotopes, version 2.1",
                " http://ie.lbl.gov/toi.",
                "The energy loss in each foil and target were calculated",
                " based on the stopping power formulae of",
                " Anderson and Ziegler."
              ]
            }
          ],
